# Implementation Plan: Standardize File Handling with Laravel Storage

Standardizing the application to use Laravel's `Storage` facade instead of manual file movements to the `public/` directory. This improves maintainability and allows for easier swapping of storage drivers (e.g., S3).

## User Review Required

> [!IMPORTANT]
> This change involves moving files from `public/` to `storage/app/public/`.
> - Existing direct links to files (if bookmarked or hardcoded outside the app) might break unless redirected.
> - `php artisan storage:link` must be executed successfully to maintain public access.

## Proposed Changes

### [Component] Helper & Infrastructure

#### [MODIFY] [helpers.php](file:///mnt/WebliesNew/CareerWithoutBarrier/career-without-barrier/app/Helper/helpers.php)
- Refactor `moveFile($path, $files)`:
  - Replace `$files->move(public_path($path), $name)` with `Storage::disk('public')->putFileAs($path, $files, $name)`.
  - Update `$image->url` generation to use `Storage::disk('public')->url($path . '/' . $name)`.
- Add `storage_url($path)` helper function as a wrapper for `Storage::disk('public')->url($path)`.

#### [EXECUTE] Migration Script
- Create a temporary script to move existing upload directories:
  - `home`
  - `upload`
  - `upload2`
  - `logos`
  - `slider`
  - `news` (if used for uploads)
- Run `php artisan storage:link`.

### [Component] Controllers

#### [MODIFY] [AdminController.php](file:///mnt/WebliesNew/CareerWithoutBarrier/career-without-barrier/app/Http/Controllers/AdminController.php)
- Update `scholarship` method and any other methods using `moveFile` to ensure they provide relative paths (without leading slashes).

### [Component] Views (Frontend & Admin)

#### [MODIFY] All Blade Files
- Perform a global replacement of hardcoded `asset()` paths for uploads:
  - `asset('home/` -> `asset('storage/home/`
  - `asset('upload/` -> `asset('storage/upload/`
  - `asset('logos/` -> `asset('storage/logos/`
  - (Better) Replace with `storage_url('home/...')` using the new helper.

